How to submit your form

1. Online: If you already receive SNAP benefits, you can use North Carolina ePASS (https://epass.nc.gov/signuphomepage) to submit this form and any proof you may need. You will need to have an enhanced account (https://epass.nc.gov/nfridp/qa) to submit these documents using ePASS.

   Instead of using ePASS, you can submit this form and any proof to your county's SNAP office <%= @county_data[:website] %><%= " or by emailing #{@county_data[:email]}" if @county_data[:email].present? %>.

2. Mail: Send your form and any proof you may need.

   <%= @county_data[:mailing_address].split("\n").join("\n   ") %>

3. In person: Print your form and bring it and any proof you may need to a local office.

   <%= @county_data[:physical_address].split("\n").join("\n   ") %>

If you have questions, or to find out if there are other ways to submit your form, you can contact your county's social services office.

- Check for information on their website <%= @county_data[:website] %>
<% if @county_data[:email].present? %>
- Email the office at <%= @county_data[:email] %>
<% end %>
- Call the office at <%= @county_data[:phone] %>
